Argentina ' s Central Puerto to build $ 140 mln plant . Argentine utility Central Puerto said Wednesday it signed a contract for local group Techint and U . S . General Electric Power Systems to build it a $ 140 million 382 MW combined cycle plant . Construction will take two years and the plant will be operative by the end of 1998 , it added in a press release . With the new plant Central Puerto , Argentina ' s biggest thermoelectric generator , will increase its installed capacity to 1 , 761 MW from 1 , 370 . Central Puerto , controlled by Chilean utilities Chilgener and Chilquinta , said the civil works will be done by Techint Compania Tecnica Internacional while the generating plant will be provided by Gnereral Electric Power Systems . - - Guillermo Haskel , Buenos Aires newsroom , 541 318 - 0650 
